# Auth-Experiment

This is an API and web project using NodeJS, ExpressJS, and MongoDB. The goal of this project is to try testing API endpoints and Web pages using Jest, Supertest, and Puppeteer.

# Features

- Register new users
- Login user and return access token
- Fetch user's profile data
- Update user's profile data
- Update user's password
- Delete user's profile data
- Logout users

# Getting Started

## Installation

Clone the repository

    npm install

## Usage

Start for development

    npm run dev

Start for production

    npm run start

Run tests

    npm run api-testB01
    npm run web-testB01
    npm run api-testB02
    npm run web-testB02
    npm run api-testB03
    npm run web-testB03
    npm run api-testB04
    npm run web-testB04
    npm run api-testB05
    npm run web-testB05
    npm run testBA


    B is the project name, and the number is the test number.
    The BA test is to test all the suits in the project.

The project can be tested using Postman to check the endpoints.

The API endpoints are:

- POST /api/v1/register -> Register new users
- POST /api/v1/login -> Login user and return access token
- GET /api/v1/profile -> Fetch user's profile data
- PATCH /api/v1/profile -> Update user's profile data
- PATCH /api/v1/profile/password -> Update user's password
- DELETE /api/v1/profile -> Delete user's profile data
- GET /api/v1/logout -> Logout users

The Web routes are:

- GET /register -> Show register form
- POST /register -> Register new users
- GET /login -> Show login form
- POST /login -> Login user and return access token
- GET /profile -> Fetch user's profile data
- GET /profile/update -> Show update profile form
- POST /profile/update -> Update user's profile data
- GET /profile/update/password -> Show update password form
- POST /profile/update/password -> Update user's password
- POST /profile/delete -> Delete user's profile data
- GET /logout -> Logout users
